@startuml
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/main/proveo.puml
title Aphelion — Overview · Durable Execution\n//layer 05 — transport / Telegram surface omitted//
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

package "Durable Execution" as DUR {
  component "**durableagent**\nchild substrate · enrollment · signatures\nsnapshots · profiles · provisioning\npolicy / conversation relay\nreview-artifact movement · forensics\ncontrol-plane HTTP · remote loop\n//continuation is not permission//" as DA <<app>>
  component "**tailnet**\noptional Tailscale substrate\nfor remote-host children" as TN <<app>>
}

' --- neighbouring layers / context ---
rectangle "Composition & Orchestration\n//-> 01-orchestration//" as ORCH <<app>>
database  "State & Continuity\n//-> 06-state//" as STATE <<db>>
cloud "Remote durable children\n(separate Linux hosts)" as REMOTE <<cloud>>

ORCH ARROW_OPTIONAL DA     : manage children
DA   ARROW_OPTIONAL TN     : remote transport
DA   ARROW_OPTIONAL STATE  : durable child state / review artifacts
TN   ARROW_CLOUD    REMOTE : signed control plane (HTTP)

note bottom of DUR
  Child reports, enrollment, wakeups, and durable
  state are **evidence** until higher governance
  grants authority. Runtime topology (parent /
  local child / remote host) is in
  ""_spec/components.puml"".
end note

@enduml
